settings.heading: About Us
settings.content: Essentials for life. Priced for living.

settings.heading: Thank You C6 Warehouse Team!
settings.text_content:
During the pandemic, our warehouse operators have shown up every day, put in tons of overtime hours and packed orders with care so that our customers, including vulnerable individuals, can keep ordering safely at home with the peace of mind that they will receive their essential goods on time.

Our operations have been at full capacity, and because our dedicated teammates show up faithfully and work around the clock, we are able to meet all orders in a timely and efficient manner.

As we continue to operate an essential service for Canadians during this difficult time, the health and safety of our customers and teammates remains a top priority. C6 is committed to providing a safe, sanitized and socially-distant work environment for our team. We are all about quality, and that applies to how we treat our staff as well.

settings.heading: We’ve grown with our customers.
settings.text_content: C6 started as a supplier of essential medical products. As our customers asked for more, we stocked more, and our team grew quickly in both size and enthusiasm. Today, we’re a full-service online retailer for everyday household and business items such as toilet paper, snacks, sanitizing wipes, air fresheners and thousands of other products.

settings.heading: Being human is a tough job.
settings.text_content:
There’s dirt you can see and germs you can’t. Businesses to run and homes to sanitize. People to care for and others to keep safe. 

We make it easier—with value pricing and same-day shipping on the products you use regularly. We keep popular brands and hard to find items in stock so you never have to hunt. And when you buy more, you’ll save more. 

Need to talk to someone about your order? Reach us by email, audio or online chat. Our customer service is what really sets us apart. We’re human, too.

settings.heading: Why our customers love us.
settings.text_content: We offer thousands of products, both niche and generic, to Canadians and provide an easy, organized and hassle-free shopping experience. Our customers know that orders are sent out same-day and shipped fast!

settings.heading: We’re a family-owned Canadian company.
settings.text_content: We’re a proudly Canadian, family-owned and operated company that’s passionate about our customers, our business, and the products we sell. Located in the heart of Ontario’s Niagara region, we’ve built our business on caring staff and quality goods.

settings.heading: We give back, because we’re looking forward.
settings.text_content:
Corporate responsibility isn't just a task on the docket, but a lifestyle.

Canadian research into spinal cord injuries is on the cutting edge. We donate 10% of our profits to help fund the next breakthrough. Why spinal cord research? Our co-founder, Eric Mukendi, experienced a spinal cord injury in 2004. We’re a business born from a need to find basic essentials at fair prices delivered reliably.

settings.heading--1:
At C6.ca , we believe we aren't just here for ourselves, but want to make a difference in other's lives. We donate 10% of our profit to programs that help differently-abled individuals live active lifestyles, such as the Power Cord Exercise Program. Spinal cord injury research is an issue that is near and dear to our hearts, so we actively look for programs to support it—but our giving doesn’t stop there.


We believe in LOCALS HELPING LOCALS and donate regularly via providing supplies or finances to various local endeavours.

settings.heading: We Give Where We Live
settings.text_content:
Find out more about how we are making a difference in Niagara:

Eric Mukendi, Co-Founder, C6 Medical - iHeartRadio.ca

settings.heading: In Recent News
settings.text_content: As we all prepare to go back to school and work environments, we all need to be thinking of ways to protect ourselves and each other. From going back into a busy office to sending our kids into the jungles that are schools, we hope our list of essentials will help make this transition a little easier and a lot safer.

settings.heading: Enjoy peace of mind that your essentials will arrive when you need them.
settings.text_content:
How our subscription service works

Just click on the subscription drop down option on the products you need and select whether you would like the item every 2 weeks, 4 weeks or 6 weeks. We’ll email you a reminder with a link to complete the order a few days before it’s due to be shipped. Simply click to complete the order - we’ll ship it out right away hassle-free.

If you don’t need the product right away, simply ignore the email notification or keep and fulfill later on. Don’t worry, we will NOT automatically charge your credit card. You are in control of your subscriptions.

settings.title: COVID - 19
settings.content: Updated as of October 2, 2020 – As the COVID-19 situation continues to evolve, we reserve the right to make any necessary changes to the information below without prior disclaimer. We will continue to adapt our practices based on the guidelines established by the Public Health Agency of Canada and local authorities.

settings.title: Ordering + Payment
settings.content: Your shopping experience is our priority, from beginning to end.

settings.headline: Is it safe to provide my credit card and personal information online?
settings.content: It is absolutely safe to use your credit card on our website. All sensitive information is transferred using the same encryption and physical security used by financial institutions.

settings.headline: What methods of payment are accepted?
settings.content: We accept Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Discover, AMEX, ApplePay, GooglePay, ShopPay and Interac E-Transfer. If you prefer to use a different method, please call us at 1 877 529-9759.

settings.headline: What is your price adjustment Policy?
settings.content: Price adjustments will be granted within 14 days of delivery or local pick-up of your orders. Certain conditions and exceptions may apply.

settings.headline: When will my order be invoiced?
settings.content: Your order will be invoiced as soon as it has been placed.

settings.headline: Will I receive a confirmation for my order?
settings.content: An order confirmation will be sent to you once your order has been placed.

settings.headline: Do you offer samples?
settings.content: If you’re ordering in bulk, there are circumstances when we can offer a sample first. Give us a call at 1 877 529-9759 and we’ll work out all the details.

settings.headline: I am on ODSP. Can I still order off the C6.ca website?
settings.content: Yes, of course! Third party insurance billings are evaluated on an individual basis. The protocol to bill these insurance companies is different and evaluated case-by-case. In some cases, we can do direct billing. If not, you’ll have the option to pay upfront and then get reimbursed by your personal insurance plan. Most private insurance companies require you to have a doctor’s prescription with diagnosis, a receipt and a claim form designed by the company. Please select the products you require and upon checkout click INSURANCE. We will contact you for more details.

settings.title: Gift Cards
settings.content: The perfect gift for someone you care about.

settings.headline: What happens if I lose my C6.ca gift card?
settings.content: C6.ca will not replace the value on a gift card in case of loss, theft or unauthorized use.

settings.headline: Does my C6.ca gift card have an expiration date?
settings.content: C6.ca gift cards do not have an expiration date.

settings.title: Subscription Service
settings.content: An easy way to organize your orders on a monthly basis.

settings.headline: How does your subscription service work?
settings.content: The C6 subscription service allows customers to ensure that they do not run out of a product. Give us a call at 1 877 529-9759 to find out more or click here.

settings.title: Shipping + Delivery
settings.content: All you need to know about getting your products right when you want it.

settings.headline: What shipping options do you offer?
settings.content: We aim to deliver our products in a timely and economical manner. All items ship via UPS with some exceptions to customer locations that might ship via Canada Post. Please visit our Shipping + Delivery page for more information.

settings.headline: How much are shipping fees?
settings.content: Shipping fees vary by product and delivery destination, which can be determined by entering your postal code when viewing your shopping cart. If your order is over $69, shipping is always free.

settings.headline: Are taxes charged on shipping fees?
settings.content: Applicable provincial and federal sales taxes are applicable on delivery fees.

settings.headline: Can my order be shipped to a PO Box?
settings.content: Yes! Canada Post will be servicing you at the nearest postal office where applicable.

settings.headline: How can I check the status of my order?
settings.content: Login to your C6.ca account to check the status of an order.

settings.headline: How can I modify or cancel my order?
settings.content: Please CONTACT US as soon as possible if you change your mind and decide to cancel or modify your order. We will be happy to provide you with suitable options based on the status of your order. Additional fees may apply to modifications being made to an order that has already been scheduled for delivery.

settings.headline: What is the pick-up process for online orders?
settings.content: Upon checking out your cart, there will be an option to pick-up from our main warehouse (which is in St Catharines, ON). You will receive an SMS notification once your order is ready for pick-up at the warehouse. Your email receipt is required at the time of pick-up.

settings.title: Returns + Exchanges
settings.content: It’s simple: we want you to be completely satisfied with your purchase.

settings.headline: What is the C6.ca return policy?
settings.content: If you are not completely satisfied with your purchase, we will gladly accept a return or exchange within ten days of delivery or pick-up, upon presentation of the original receipt. The unused item must be returned in its original condition and packaging. Refunds will be processed based on the original method of payment. Customers are responsible for the applicable delivery fees for the return or exchange of the product(s) that want to be returned.

settings.headline: How can I return merchandise?
settings.content: Please CONTACT US within ten days of delivery or pick-up to arrange a return or exchange. To arrange a return or exchange for an online order, please call us at 1 877 529-9759.

settings.headline: What should I do if my merchandise arrives damaged or defective?
settings.content: Please CONTACT US as soon as possible with a detailed description of the issue along with a photo. We’ll take care of the rest.

settings.title: Company Information
settings.content: Curious about us? Your answers are here.

settings.headline: Is C6.ca a Canadian company?
settings.content: Yes! We’re located in the heart of the Niagara Region in St Catharines, Ontario.

settings.headline: Are prices in Canadian dollars?
settings.content: Yes, all of our product pricing is in Canadian currency.

settings.content: Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet

settings.headline: Learn about our super-fast shipping.
settings.content: Our products are shipped across Canada from our C6 warehouse in the Niagara region: We use several couriers including UPS, FedEx, Canada Post and many more to ensure your orders arrive as soon as possible. Free delivery on all orders over $69+.

settings.headline: Same-day delivery & 24H shipping within the GTA
settings.content:
We are pleased to offer same-day delivery when orders are placed before 8am EST within the Greater Toronto Area*. Orders over $69+ enjoy the added benefit of FREE same-day delivery. At check-out, delivery availability and options will appear where available (service map). Any orders that are placed after 8am EST will arrive the next day.

* In cases where package dimensions and weight are exceptional; orders will be shipped by ground.
